  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Crankshaft pulley removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Right side front wheel removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000659",
          "label": "Right side front wheel removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Right side front splash guard removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000849",
          "label": "Right side front splash guard removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Crankshaft Pulley TDC mark Alignment"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "368_5.0_jpn_11582756_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Rotate the crankshaft pulley in a clockwise direction to align the alignment mark (A) with the TDC mark (white marking) (B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Confirmation shall be made from the specified viewing direction (C)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. A.C. generator belt removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000351",
          "label": "A.C. generator belt removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Water pump Belt removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000433",
          "label": "Water pump Belt removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "6. Remove side engine mount bracket mounting nut"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "368_5.0_jpn_11582757_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Place the oil pan on a plate and support it with a garage jack. Remove the side engine mount bracket mounting nut."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "7. Crankshaft pulley removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "368_5.0_jpn_11582758_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Lower the engine. Pulley Holder Attachment 50x25 (07JAB-0010400), Handle 6-25-660L (07JAB-001020B), and Socket Wrench 19 Use the 90L (07JAA-001020A) to remove the crankshaft pulley."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Do not lower the engine too much."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Crankshaft pulley Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "368_5.0_jpn_11582759_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Before installing the crankshaft pulley, do the following Wipe off dirt with a rag. Oil application: Apply oil."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Never use an impact wrench."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Crankshaft pulley Tightening (when pulley bolts or crankshaft is replaced)"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "368_5.0_jpn_11582760_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Pulley Holder Attachment 50x25 (07JAB-0010400), Handle 6-25-660L (07JAB-001020B), Socket Wrench 19 Tighten the pulley bolts to 30 N-m (3.1 kgf-m) using the 90L (07JAA-001020A) and a torque wrench."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "368_5.0_jpn_11582761_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Tighten the pulley bolts 90°. Remove the pulley bolt."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "368_5.0_jpn_11582762_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "4",
      "text": "Tighten the pulley bolts to 46 N-m (4.7 kgf-m). Tighten the pulley bolts 90°."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Crankshaft pulley tightening (when pulley bolts and crankshaft are reused)"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "368_5.0_jpn_11582763_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Pulley Holder Attachment 50x25 (07JAB-0010400), Handle 6-25-660L (07JAB-001020B), Socket Wrench 19 Tighten the pulley bolts to 46 N-m (4.7 kgf-m) using 90L (07JAA-001020A) and a torque wrench."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "368_5.0_jpn_11582764_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Tighten the pulley bolts 90°."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Front bumper removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000814",
          "label": "Front bumper removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Front upper grille removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000842",
          "label": "Front upper grille removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "6. Right side front bulkhead box removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "368_5.0_jpn_11677567_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "7. Tighten side engine mount brackets."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "368_5.0_jpn_11582765_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Temporarily tighten the new side engine mount bracket mounting nut (A) and loosen the side engine mount bracket mounting bolt (B). Perform the side engine mount tightening procedure.",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000357",
          "label": "Perform the side engine mount tightening procedure.",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "If the side engine mount bracket fasteners are removed, the transmission mount and torque rod must be tightened in the correct sequence."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "8. Right side front bulkhead box installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "368_5.0_jpn_11677568_3.0_disp.png"
    },
